<HEAD>Pennsylvanians Caught With Fake Credentials</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of Pennsylvanians was so eager to hear
Gov. Robert P. Casey address the Democratic National Convention
that they used fake credentials to enter The Omni, said
Pennsylvania state chairman Larry Yatch.
   ``It was just people who were a little overzealous,'' Yatch said
Wednesday after six members of the group were forced to leave the
convention hall.
   After the discovery, security was tightened at entrances to The
Omni, and credentials were scanned by special laser devices to
check for authenticity.
</TEXT>
