<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0334</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rain in Midwest, Northeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms fell in much of the nation today,
including the drought-blighted Midwest and South.
   Rain fell from Ohio to Mississippi and central Texas, and from
southwest Arizona to Southern California.
   Showers and thunderstorms also fell from southern Maine to
Maryland and from southern New York to West Virginia.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from New
England to the upper Ohio Valley and the Appalachians, scattered
over the central and lower Great Lakes and from the Middle Atlantic
States to Florida, Gulf Coast states and the southeast third of
Texas.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 80s or 90s across much of
the nation, the 70s from the upper Great Lakes to the upper Ohio
Valley and northern and central New England; from 100 to 110
degrees from the desert Southwest to Nevada, in much of Oregon and
in southern Washington; and near 120 degrees in sections of
southwest Arizona and the Southern California deserts.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 44
degrees at Custer, S.D., to 96 degrees at Nellis Air Force Base
near Las Vegas, Nev.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 77 fair; Boston 66 showers; Buffalo 69 showers;
Charleston, S.C. 78 fair; Cincinnati 67 foggy; Cleveland 65 rain;
Detroit 68 cloudy; Miami 79 fair; New York 73 foggy; Philadelphia
75 foggy; Pittsburgh 68 showers; Portland, Maine 67 rain;
Washington 77 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 54 fair; Chicago 69 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth
74 fair; Denver 59 fair; Des Moines 59 fair; Indianapolis 63 fair;
Kansas City 59 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 58 fair; Nashville 74
foggy; New Orleans 78 partly cloudy; St. Louis 70 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 67 fair; Anchorage 57 cloudy; Las Vegas 93
fair; Los Angeles 69 cloudy; Phoenix 84 cloudy; Salt Lake City 71
fair; San Diego 70 fair; San Francisco 58 fair; Seattle 64 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 66 partly cloudy; Toronto 70 hazy.
</TEXT>
