<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Cruise,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cruise: Nothing Romantic About Movie Love Scenes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heartthrob Tom Cruise says growing up with three
sisters helped him learn to understand women, but he confesses
there's not much real romance in front of the camera.
   ``With sisters, you always got the inside scoop on what they
thought about their boyfriends and what women like,'' he says in
the Aug. 8 issue of Us magazine.
   Still, doing love scenes ``is not a comfortable situation for
anyone,'' says Cruise, the star of ``Risky Business,'' ``Top Gun''
and ``The Color of Money.''
   ``There is nothing romantic about 20 guys behind the camera,
telling you to move to your left and, `Sorry, we missed that shot.'
''
   Cruise's ninth movie, ``Cocktail,'' opens later this month.
</TEXT>
