<1ST_LINE>r p AM-CVN--CampaignWedding     07-21 0200</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CVN--Campaign Wedding,200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dukakis Aides Plan A Marriage Of Politics and Love</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steve Akey and Joyce Carrier, top aides to
Michael Dukakis, have had a frantic Democratic National Convention
week dealing with vital questions of logistics, media _ and mother.
   Mother is the one planning their wedding next week.
   ``Yesterday's question was what kind of champagne glasses do we
want,'' said Akey, whose job was running the press center at
Dukakis' hotel.
   Akey and Ms. Carrier, Dukakis' national director of advance
work, met in Boston during the early days of the campaign. Their
desks were next to each other in Boston, and they immediately
struck up a rapport.
   ``I've worked for Dukakis since '83 so I knew all about Michael
Dukakis and nothing about presidential campaigning and she knew
presidential campaigning and nothing about Michael Dukakis,'' he
said. ``So we had a lot of sessions at the lobby bar and we became
best friends.''
   Dukakis' nomination runs a close second to the excitement of the
July 30 wedding, Akey said, even though Ms. Carrier's mother has
had to handle the arrangements.
   And will the man who brought them together attend?
   ``No, he'll be campaigning,'' Akey said.
</TEXT>
