<HEAD>Release Date Of Former Rajneeshee Pushed Back</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs last graf to CORRECT by deleting `Indian.'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The former chief aide to Indian guru
Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh has been transferred to a federal prison in
San Diego and her release date pushed back because of ``prohibited
activity,'' a prosecutor says.
   Ma Anand Sheela, 39, was disciplined for activity that took
place in April at the federal prison at Pleasanton, Calif., Barry
Sheldahl, assistant U.S. attorney in Portland, said Wednesday. He
refused to elaborate.
   Sheela's release has been moved from Dec. 19 to Jan. 8, Sheldahl
said.
   She is serving a 4{-year sentence for crimes ranging from arson
and attempted murder to immigration fraud, electronic eavesdropping
and masterminding a food-poisoning outbreak that made 750 people
sick.
   Sheela pleaded guilty in 1986.
   The commune she helped run at Rajneeshpuram disbanded after
Rajneesh pleaded guilty to an immigration charge and was deported
in 1985.
