<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Brites     07-21 0367</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brites,0383</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bright and Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESTPORT, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A town by any other name wouldn't make it.
   A group holds a convention every year in a different city but
never anywhere but Westport. The annual World Convention of
Westports always is in one Westport or another.
   This year's was in New Zealand and next year's will be in
Massachusetts, probably in August, says Westport, Mass., Selectman
George T. Leach Jr.
   The convention of the 23 Westports around the world _ 17 in the
United States, three in Canada, and one each in Ireland, England
and New Zealand _ was the brainchild of Westport, Mo., Mayor Robert
Regan in 1983.
   It came after he visited Westport, Ireland, then invited the
Irish mayor to help his Westport celebrate its 150th anniversary.
   Previous conventions have been held in the Westports of Ireland
and New York.
   ``It's kind of a nice thing,'' Leach said of the planned meeting
in the Bay State. ``We'll get a lot of publicity.''
   The 1990 convention will be held in Westport, Conn., home to
actor Paul Newman and talk show host Phil Donahue and considered
the toniest of the Westports.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steve Tucker is hoping he can come up with
the ransom _ 350 pennies and Mexican beer.
   The hostage: his family's plastic pink flamingo.
   When 9-year-old Michael Tucker went to get the mail Saturday, he
found a note with it.
   The note, patched together from letters cut out of papers and
magazines, read, ``We've got the bird,'' said Steve Tucker,
Michael's father. ``Then all it said was, `We will be contacting
you soon.'''
   A pile of pink feathers was found where the 2{-foot flamingo,
purchased two weeks ago for $3.15, had been staked into the lawn.
   ``He must have put up a violent struggle,'' Tucker said
Wednesday.
   The Groups Against Gaudy Yard Art _ the kind of art that's
enough to GAGYA _ claimed responsibility for the abduction. A
spokesman for the group said the bird is unharmed.
   The next ransom note demanded the pennies and one bottle of an
exotic beer. Tucker says he's never heard of the beer _ Carta
Blanca _ and is awaiting further instructions.
</TEXT>
