<1ST_LINE>r p AM-CVN--SecurityBreach     07-21 0189</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CVN--Security Breach,200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Counterfeit Credentials Confiscated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities on Wednesday said they confiscated
several counterfeit delegate credentials being worn by persons in
the Pennsylvania delegation.
   One volunteer working for the Pennsylvania state committee was
leaving the floor when a security person noticed she was wearing a
fake credential, confiscated it and removed the volunteer from the
convention arena, said Karen Balaban, counsel to the state
committee.
   She said the volunteer was handed the credential by a woman
while they were riding to the convention center from the suburban
hotel where the delegation is staying.
   Security officials then checked the entire delegation and five
people were escorted from the center, said Pennsylvania state
chairman Larry Yatch.
   After the discovery, security was tightened at the entrances to
The Omni, site of the Democratic gathering, with credentials being
scanned by special laser devices to check for authenticity.
   Yatch said he explained to security that a number of people
without credentials had wanted to get into the Omni to hear
Pennsylvania Gov. Robert P. Casey address the convention.
   ``It was just people who were a little over zealous,'' Yatch
said.
</TEXT>
