<1ST_LINE>r a AM-OfficerShot     07-21 0311</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Officer Shot,0322</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Vice Officer Shot To Death During Robbery Attempt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A vice officer shot twice during a robbery
attempt at an adult bookstore begged an assailant not to shoot him
a third time, but the gunman fired anyway, killing him, police said
Wednesday.
   Houston Police Officer Elston Howard, who was to married in two
weeks, was behind the counter with a clerk at the 24-hour bookstore
late Tuesday writing a citation when the gunman walked in, police
said.
   Howard, 26, was not in uniform but wore a police raid jacket
with HPD on it and had his gun, said homicide Sgt. John Silva. The
gunman shot Howard when the officer looked up.
   Howard struggled briefly with the gunman then fell to the floor,
Silva said. The officer never drew his gun.
   Witnesses told police the gunman stood over Howard as the
officer begged him not to shoot again, but he did anyway.
   ``It was just a straight, cold-blooded execution,'' Silva said.
   ``(The gunman) was in the process of conducting an aggravated
robbery and the last thing he expected to see was an HPD officer,''
Silva said. ``So, instead of bailing out, he just went ahead and
shot the officer.''
   The gunman then robbed the clerk, telling him, ``Give me the
money or you're going to be next,'' Silva said. The man fled in a
vehicle with a small amount of cash.
   Howard's partner was in the process of moving their unmarked
police car when the shooting occurred and did not realize what had
happened, police said.
   Howard, shot three times, was pronounced dead at Ben Taub
Hospital. He had been with the police department for five years.
   Police believe the gunman also may have been involved in the
robbery of another adult book store earlier Tuesday. No arrests had
been made in the case late Wednesday.
</TEXT>
