<TEXT>
   The stock market advanced Wednesday in a dull session. The Dow
Jones average of 30 industrials climbed 13.34 points to close at
2,110.60.
   The dollar rebounded after falling overseas amid reports of some
central bank intervention. Gold prices were mixed.
   Bond prices were mostly unchanged to slightly lower.
   Oil prices rebounded, but soybean futures prices plunged the
permissible limit, oat futures fell sharply, wheat was lower and
corn was mixed.
