<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0177</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Higher At Midday In Light Dealings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rose slightly Thursday in the absence
of either concerted buying or selling pressure.
   Dealers said a spate of takeover rumors that energized the
market earlier in the session ran out of steam by midday, leaving
players uncertain over the near-term direction for equities.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was 1.4
points, or 0.07 percent, higher at 1,868.6. Trading volume was a
light 232.1 million shares, compared with 192.5 million shares at
the same time Wednesday.
   Many players said they were sticking to the sidelines ahead of
Wall Street's opening. Several dealers predicted the New York
market would open sharply lower in the wake of surging commodity
prices, sparking fears of inflation.
   Some said the market was taking a rest after the pronounced
movements over the course of the week.
   ``There just isn't any business around,'' one equity salesman
said, adding that the market ``needs a spark of something to set it
alight.''
