<HEAD>PPG Profit Up 31 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   PPG Industries Inc. said Thursday surging
sales and operating earnings boosted the glass, coating and
chemical company's profits 31 percent in the second quarter.
   PPG said it earned $133.8 million, or $1.22 per share, compared
to $102.4 million, or 85 cents per share, in the second three
months of 1987.
   Sales rose 9 percent from $1.33 billion to $1.45 billion.
   ``Sales growth was achieved globally in virtually every major
product category,'' said Chairman Vincent A. Sarni. ``International
expansion and diversification, together with greater efficiency and
cost control, are important elements of the company's rapid
performance growth.''
   For the first half, PPG's earnings increased 33 percent to
$252.4 million, or $2.29 per share, from $189.3 million, or $1.58
per share.
   Sales were up 9 percent to $2.82 billion from $2.6 billion in
the first half of last year.
