<1ST_LINE>r f BC-AutoProdn     07-21 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
159,519 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
132,693, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's anticipated production is higher than the same week
a year ago, in which 138,464 cars and light trucks were produced,
the trade journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 88,879 cars this week,
compared with 93,982 a week ago and 74,130 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 70,640,
compared with last week's 38,711 and last year's 64,334.
   Canadian automakers were to build 5,654 cars this week, down
from 8,568 a week ago and down from last year's 8,537.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 5,170, compared
with 6,015 a week ago and 3,393 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
