<2ND_LINE>AM-Germany-Airbus,0116</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lufthansa Orders Four Airbuses Worth $270 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The West German airline Lufthansa
on Thursday said it will purchase four additional Airbus jets for a
total of about $270 million.
   Three of the planes are A300-310s and one is a larger A300-600.
All of the planes can carry about 200 passengers.
   The purchase of an additional four planes will bring the
carrier's fleet of Airbus planes to 28.
   Delivery is scheduled to take place between November 1989 and
February 1990.
   Airbus Industrie is a consortium comprising Aerospatiale of
France, British Aerospace PLC, Spain's Construccionnes Aeronauticas
SA and Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm GmbH of West Germany.
</TEXT>
