<HEAD>Stocks Slip</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout with London close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices fell Thursday on the London Stock Exchange
after a trendless session.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index slipped 2.8
points, or 0.15 percent, to 1,864.4.
   Trading volume was 400.2 million shares, compared with
Wednesday's 445.0 million shares.
   Analysts said investors were taking a cautious stance until they
had a better feel for the direction of the dollar and oil prices.
   ``There are lots of questions without many answers at the
moment,'' said one equity salesman, adding that the market ``won't
power one way or another because there are too many contradictory
forces at work.''
   ``There's no feel of direction for this market,'' another dealer
said.
</TEXT>
