<1ST_LINE>d f AM-Earns-Scott     07-21 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Scott,0198</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reports Higher 2nd-Qtr Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Scott Paper Co. said Wednesday its
second-quarter earnings rose 28.1 percent, and cited the
performance of its international personal care and domestic
printing and publishing papers businesses.
   Scott said it earned $75.3 million, or 98 cents per share, in
the second quarter, compared with $58.8 million, or 77 cents per
share, a year earlier.
   Second-quarter sales rose to $1.16 billion from $1.03 billion a
year earlier.
   Combined sales for Scott Worldwide's personal care and cleaning
business rose 14 percent from last year. The company attributed the
increase to record sales volume and higher prices for some products.
   Sales rose 11 percent and income from operations was up 34
percent for S.D. Warren's printing and publishing papers business.
The increases were attributed to strong demand for coated papers _
Warren's principal business _ combined with price increases
announced in 1987.
   For the first six months of the year, Scott reported its earned
$149.3 million, or $1.95 a share, up from $107.8 million, or $1.41
a share, a year earlier. Six-month revenue rose to $2.29 billion
from $1.99 billion a year earlier.
</TEXT>
